The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 26: Public sector banks will hire 30,000 personnel during 2009-10 even as India Inc  faced with the global financial meltdown  has put a virtual halt on recruitment, M. Balachandran, director of the Institute of Banking Personnel Selection, said. The institute has been assisting the financial sector in the selection, promotion and placement of employees.                             
	 New Delhi, April 26: The income tax department will make it mandatory for firms to submit information online before remitting payments to foreign companies from July to plug loopholes.                            
	 New Delhi, April 26: The World Banks private sector lending arm, the International Finance Corporation, will invest $1 billion in Indian companies during its financial year beginning June 2009, IFC director for infrastructure (Asia and Africa), Anita George, said.                             
	 New Delhi, April 26: Indias gems and jewellery exports, which had taken a severe beating in the second half of the last fiscal, are expected to regain their shine from September 2009-10, Gitanjali group managing director Mehul Choksi said.                            
	 New Delhi, April 26: The aviation industry is poised for another round of consolidation as early as the first half of the current fiscal, with low-cost carriers such as IndiGo and SpiceJet requiring significant capital and fund inflow, the Centre for Asia Pacific Aviation said.                                                                                                                           
